[b]Fixing the "null" printing in the console, which also prevents the server from crashing over time[/b]
First of, a brief explanation of why the "null" prints out is because whoever made the server base you use was retarded. Instead of using the common [i]printStackTrace[/i] method when an exception is caught, they made the [i]println[/i] method print out the message of the exception. This was "null".

Second, it happens because there's an unknown bug with friends loading (I never paid much attention to it). So, to get started, open your client class. Look for this (It's towards of the bottom of the login actions):
[code]		boolean pmloaded = false;

		for (long element : friends) {[/code]Replace that whole for loop and the next one with this code:
[code]		for (long element : friends) {
			if (element != 0) {
				for (int i2 = 1; i2 < handler.maxPlayers; i2++) {
					if (server.playerHandler.players[i2] != null)
					{
						if(server.playerHandler.players[i2].playerName != null)
						{
							if(handler.players[i2].isActive && (misc.playerNameToInt64(handler.players[i2].playerName) == element))
							{
								if ((playerRights >= 2) || (handler.players[i2].Privatechat == 0) || ((handler.players[i2].Privatechat == 1) && handler.players[i2].isinpm(misc.playerNameToInt64(playerName))))
								{
									loadpm(element, GetWorld(i2));
									pmloaded = true;
								}
								break;
							}
						}
					}
				}
				if (!pmloaded) {
					loadpm(element, 0);
				}
				pmloaded = false;
			}
		}
		for (int i1 = 1; i1 < handler.maxPlayers; i1++) {
			if ((handler.players[i1] != null)
					&& (handler.players[i1].isActive == true)) {
				handler.players[i1].pmupdate(playerId, GetWorld(playerId));
			}
		}[/code]As for what this does, as it's just a matter of checking for unassigned variables before using them. I'm not going to tell you how to fix the printing of "null", as there's only two places that I can recall that print the message of the exception, so it's not hard to find.

